  "editorial": {
    "headline": "Soderstrom's Tenth-Inning Single Lifts Oakland Past Chicago Cubs",
    "subheadline": "ATH 5, CHC 4 in a marathon that went to the 10th.",
    "lead_angle": "Tyler Soderstrom drove a tenth-inning single into center field, plating the automatic runner and finally putting the Oakland Athletics ahead for good. The Athletics edged the Chicago Cubs 5-4 in a marathon afternoon at Wrigley Field.\n\nThe Chicago Cubs had seized control early, taking a 4-2 lead into the eighth behind solo home runs from Pete Crow-Armstrong in the second and Seiya Suzuki in the third. But the Oakland Athletics found life in the eighth. Colby Thomas connected for a solo home run, cutting the lead. Another run scored later in the frame, knotting the score and forcing extra innings at Wrigley.\n\nSoderstrom finished with two hits and two runs batted in, driving in the crucial tenth-inning score against losing pitcher Ethan Roberts. Hogan Harris earned the victory for Oakland, with Justin Sterner recording the save. This road win keeps the Athletics in the thick of the American League playoff chase, while the Cubs now face renewed pressure in a tight National League Central division battle.",
    "reason": "Marathon ball. 10 innings of sustained tension makes this the day's standout."
  },
